data.enText: to leave a place, especially to start a trip

data.chText: 飞往罗马的班机从3号航站楼出发。
data.enText: Flights for Rome depart from Terminal 3.

data.chText: 她一直等到最后一个客人离开。
data.enText: She waited until the last of the guests had departed.

data.chText: 火车在下午6点15分离开了阿姆利则。
data.enText: The train departed Amritsar at 6.15 p.m.

data.chText: 离开人世，去世，亡故（委婉说法，与die同义）
data.enText: to die. People say depart this life to avoid saying die .
to behave in a way that is different from usual

data.chText: 她一反常态乘公共汽车上班了。
data.enText: Departing from her usual routine, she took the bus to work.

simple_means.memory_skill: de 加强 + part 部分；分开 → 分开 → 离开

ex.chText: 这趟航班将于上午10点在希思罗机场起飞。
ex.enText: The flight will depart Heathrow Airport at 10 o'clock.

ex.chText: 他星期五出发去伦敦了。
ex.enText: He departed for London on Friday.

ex.chText: 这位即将离职的校长建议学校关注教学质量。
ex.enText: The departing headmaster suggested that the school focus on education quality.

synonyms.bx: 较正式用词，尤指动身去旅行。

ex.chText: 小偷看见警察过来便马上溜走了。
ex.enText: The thief cleared off when he saw the cops coming.
You shouldn't be here. Clear off!

ex.chText: 敌人逃到附近的另一个村子去了。
ex.enText: The enemy decamped to another village nearby.

ex.chText: 富裕的居民从市中心逃走了。
ex.enText: The wealthier residents decamped from downtown.

ex.chText: 那名会计把所有的钱卷走逃跑了。
ex.enText: That accountant decamped with all the money.

synonyms.bx: 指迅速逃跑，常与介词 to/from 连用。

data.enText: to die. People say depart this life to avoid saying die .

data.chText: 她一反常态乘公共汽车上班了。
data.enText: Departing from her usual routine, she took the bus to work.

tr: move away from a place into another direction
example: Go away before I start to cry
The family took off for Florida

tr: wander from a direct or straight course
remove oneself from an association with or participation in
example: She left her position with the Red Cross
He left the Senate after two terms
after 20 years with the same company, she pulled up stakes

value.def: When something or someone departs from a place, they leave it and start a journey to another place.

example.ex: Our tour departs from Heathrow Airport on 31 March and returns 16 April...
example.tran: 我们这次旅行于 3月 31 号从希思罗机场出发，4 月 16 号返回。

example.ex: In the morning Mr McDonald departed for Sydney...
example.tran: 麦克唐纳先生上午启程前往悉尼。

example.ex: The coach departs Potsdam in the morning.
example.tran: 长途客车早上从波茨坦开出。

value.def: If you depart from a traditional, accepted, or agreed way of doing something, you do it in a different or unexpected way.

example.ex: Why is it in this country that we have departed from good educational sense?...
example.tran: 为什么在这个国家我们背离了教育上明智的选择？

example.ex: It takes a brave cook to depart radically from the traditional Christmas menu.
example.tran: 一个厨师要彻底颠覆传统的圣诞节菜肴是需要很大勇气的。

value.def: If someone departs from a job, they resign from it or leave it. In American English, you can say that someone departs a job.

example.ex: Lipton is planning to depart from the company he founded.
example.tran: 利普顿打算离开他创立的那家公司。

example.ex: ...a number of staff departed during his reign as rector of the Royal College of Art...
example.tran: 在他担任皇家艺术学院院长期间有好几名教师辞职了。
他在 20 世纪 60 年代告别了棒球场。

value.def: When someone departs this life, or departs this earth, they die.

example.ex: He departed this world with a sense of having fulfilled his destiny.
example.tran: 他带着一种已完成使命的满足感离开了这个世界。

de 加强 + part 部分；分开 → 分开 → 离开
de 向下 + part 部分；分开 + ment 表组织、机构 → 向下分成各个部分 → 部门；系
im 进入 + part 部分；分开 →〔引导〕进入〔知识的〕一部分 → 传授；告知

im 不 + part 部分；分开 + ible 可…的 → 不能分成部分的 → 不可分的
